  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\n`kubectl create deployment` does not work if we specify docker image\r\nwith hash.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ kubectl create deployment mariadb  --image=docker.io/centos/mariadb-102-centos7@sha256:fca5b3ad8e9887beeeebb49f71dd3d0d62c94632d6cfdee74192f68309e95ceb\r\nThe Deployment \"mariadb\" is invalid: spec.template.spec.containers[0].name: Invalid value: \"mariadb-102-centos7@sha256\": a DNS-1123 label must consist of lower case alphanumeric characters or '-', and must start and end with an alphanumeric character (e.g. 'my-name',  or '123-abc', regex used for validation is '[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?')\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\n- container name should drop `@sha256` from `mariadb-102-centos7@sha256`.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nJust following one command only\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ kubectl create deployment mariadb  --image=docker.io/centos/mariadb-102-centos7@sha256:fca5b3ad8e9887beeeebb49f71dd3d0d62c94632d6cfdee74192f68309e95ceb\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nProposal patch: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/62253 \r\n",
